# ðŸŒŽ GCP Security Standard v1.0

**Version:** 1.0  
**Applicable To:** All teams using Google Cloud Platform (GCP) for workloads, data, APIs, hosting, storage, CI/CD, or service accounts.  

**Scope:**  
- IAM & Identity Federation  
- Compute (GKE, GCE, Cloud Run, App Engine)  
- Storage (GCS, Filestore)  
- Networking & Firewalls  
- Cloud Build / Cloud Deploy  
- Secrets & Keys  
- Logging, Monitoring, Data Security  

---

## ðŸŽ¯ Objective

To ensure secure deployment, management, and scaling of cloud workloads while protecting identities, data, supply chain artifacts, keys, and network infrastructure from unauthorized access and compromise.

---

## ðŸ” 1. Identity & Authentication (SSO / MFA / Workload Identity)

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| User identity | Must use **SSO via Google Workspace / Entra / Okta**; no personal gmail accounts. |
| MFA enforcement | Mandatory for all users with GCP access. |
| Service accounts | Must not be used for human access. |
| Workload identity | Must use **Workload Identity Federation** instead of static keys. |
| Keyless auth | CI/CD tools must authenticate via **OIDC Federation**, not key files. |

---

## ðŸ”‘ 2. IAM & Least-Privilege Access

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Role policy | Only predefined least-privilege roles allowed (no `Owner`, no custom wide roles). |
| User roles | Must be granted via Google Workspace groups, not individuals. |
| Service accounts | Must be scoped to a single workload & environment. |
| Admins | Restricted to **â‰¤ 5 central cloud security administrators**. |
| External users | Approved only by Security + Expire every **90 days**. |

---

## ðŸ”’ 3. Key Management, Secrets, and Access Credentials

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Secret storage | All passwords, keys, tokens, API secrets must be stored in **Secret Manager**. |
| Key rotation | Automatic rotation required for CMKs + manual yearly review. |
| Key usage logs | KMS CryptoKey access logs must be forwarded to SIEM. |
| No static keys | Prohibited for CI/CD pipelines and deployed workloads. |
| OAuth credentials | Must enforce least scopes, short lifetime tokens, and IP restrictions. |

---

## ðŸ›¡ 4. Network & Firewall Security

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Default networks | Default VPCs must be deleted; no public ingress. |
| Firewall | Explicit allow rules; deny by default. |
| External access | Public IPs prohibited for workloads unless approved. |
| Private access | Use Private Google Access for GCR, API, Artifact calls. |
| Encryption in transit | Must use TLS 1.2+; internal services use mTLS when supported. |

---

## ðŸ“¦ 5. Supply Chain Security (Artifacts, AI Models, Containers, CI/CD)

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Artifact registry | Only **Artifact Registry** or approved private registries allowed. |
| Image scanning | Mandatory vulnerability scan for each deploy (Container Analysis/Scanner). |
| Build provenance | Must use **SLSA-compliant Cloud Build provenance**. |
| npm/pip security | Internet registry access must go via private mirror/proxy. |
| AI/ML models | Stored in isolated secured storage with private network. |

---

## âš™ï¸ 6. Compute & Workload Security

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| GKE | Must use Workload Identity, Pod-level IAM, and Node Auto-Upgrade. |
| Cloud Run | Must run as dedicated service account, no root privileges. |
| VM security | Must enforce OS patching, Shielded VM & secure boot. |
| App Engine | Must use identity-aware firewall + private networking. |
| Data access | Workloads must not use keys; only OIDC + IAM bindings. |

---

## ðŸ”‘ 7. Secrets & Environment Variables (Prod Workloads)

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Secrets | Must not be stored in Cloud Build YAML, Dockerfiles, Terraform, or source code. |
| Runtime retrieval | Only via Secret Manager & workload identity. |
| Rotations | Business critical secrets rotated every **90 days**. |
| Exposure monitoring | Secret access logs must alert on unusual access patterns. |

---

## ðŸ§ª 8. Logging, Monitoring, & Security Command Center

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Audit logs | Must be enabled org-wide (Admin, Data, Access logs). |
| Log retention | Minimum retention = **1 year**. |
| SCC | Security Command Center (SCC) must be enabled at **Enterprise level**. |
| Alerting required for |  
- IAM changes  
- Key usage  
- New external IPs  
- Firewall rule changes  
- Secret access anomalous requests |
| SIEM | Logs must be streamed to central SIEM (Splunk/Sentinel/Elastic). |

---

## ðŸš¨ 9. Data Security & Storage

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Default encryption | Must use Google-managed encryption or CMEK when sensitive. |
| Bucket policies | Public access disabled org-wide; required uniform bucket-level access. |
| Sensitive buckets | Must enforce VPC Service Controls + Access Justification. |
| Object versioning | Must be enabled for sensitive storage. |

---

## ðŸ” 10. Governance, Audits, and Continuous Compliance

| Requirement | Standard |
|-------------|----------|
| Quarterly review | IAM roles, service accounts, keys, firewall rules. |
| Annual audit | Workload identity, data sensitivity, pipeline security. |
| Policy review | Updated annually by Security Leadership. |
| Enforcement | Non-compliant workloads may be disabled or blocked from deployment. |

---

## ðŸ“„ Appendices

### ðŸ“Œ A. Enforcement Priorities

| Priority | Controls |
|----------|----------|
| **P1 (Immediate)** | SSO + MFA, Delete default networks, Secret Manager usage |
| **P2 (30 Days)** | Workload identity, private registry, SCC enablement |
| **P3 (Quarterly)** | SIEM streaming, artifact signing, VPC service controls |

---

### ðŸ“Œ B. Approved Security Tools

| Function | Tools |
|----------|-------|
| CI/CD Provenance | Cloud Build + SLSA |
| Container Scanning | Container Analysis, Artifact Scanner |
| Secrets | Secret Manager |
| IAM Review | IAM Recommender |
| FinOps + Audit | SCC, Forseti, Cloud Asset Inventory |
| IaC Scanning | Terraform Validator, Checkov, Polaris |

---

### ðŸ“Œ C. Enforcement Clause

> Failure to comply with this GCP Security Standard may result in suspension of impacted workloads, revocation of privileged access, or denial of deployments until required remediation is completed.

